      type: "Pooled human immunoglobulin G (immunomodulatory agent)",
      action: "Modulates the dysregulated immune response through multiple mechanisms: Fc receptor blockade on macrophages, neutralization of pathogenic cytokines (IL-1, IL-6, TNF-alpha), inhibition of complement activation, and modulation of T-cell and B-cell function; reduces coronary artery aneurysm formation from 25% to approximately 4% when given within the first 10 days",
      sideEffects: "Infusion reactions (headache, fever, chills, flushing, nausea, myalgia), hypotension, aseptic meningitis (delayed headache and nuchal rigidity 24-48 hours post-infusion), hemolytic anemia (anti-A and anti-B antibodies in IVIG), anaphylaxis (rare, higher risk in IgA-deficient patients), thrombotic events (rare)",
