        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Aspirin use during varicella (chickenpox) or influenza infection increases the risk of Reye syndrome in children. Although the risk is lower with antiplatelet doses, aspirin should be temporarily discontinued and an alternative antiplatelet agent (dipyridamole or clopidogrel) substituted until the varicella infection resolves. The provider must be contacted for medication adjustment."
