        rationale: "IVIG contains pooled antibodies from thousands of donors, including antibodies against measles, mumps, rubella, and varicella. These passive antibodies neutralize the live attenuated vaccine viruses before the child's immune system can mount its own response, resulting in vaccine failure. The 11-month deferral allows time for the passive antibodies to decline sufficiently for effective vaccination."
