        options: ["Acute phase (days 1-11) when fever is highest","Subacute phase (days 11-21) when platelet counts peak and aneurysms develop","Convalescent phase (days 21-60+) when laboratory values normalize","Recovery phase (beyond 60 days) when all symptoms have resolved"],
        correct: 1,
        rationale: "The subacute phase is paradoxically the highest-risk period: fever resolves and the child appears to improve clinically, but platelet counts peak dramatically (often exceeding 1,000,000), coronary aneurysms reach maximum size, and the combination of aneurysmal dilation with extreme thrombocytosis creates the highest risk for coronary thrombosis, MI, and sudden death."
